        </isunsigned>
        <isfloat>
          no
        </isfloat>
        <description>
          The master router&apos;s real IP address.  The master router would set this address to vrrpv3OperationsPrimaryIpAddr while transitioning to master state.  For backup routers, this is the IP address listed as the source in the VRRP advertisement last received by this virtual router.
        </description>
        <OriginalOID>
          1.3.6.1.2.1.207.1.1.1.1.3
        </OriginalOID>
